EMP_NOTES: 12/2/2024 12:41:36 Jodie.Cleverly - Recd email to Appship Inbox which Terry was copied in Hi Terry I trust this email finds you well. I'm reaching out to express my concerns about my on-the-job training as outlined in my training plan for the Boilermaking/Welding Fabrication trade apprenticeship. Since starting my apprenticeship I've been keen to learn and develop my skills per the duties and responsibilities set out in the training plan. However I've noticed a significant gap between the outlined expectations and the opportunities provided for me to follow progress and grow within these parameters. Specifically I've encountered challenges in accessing the necessary practical experiences and mentorship required to grasp and master the essential aspects of the trade fully. Despite my proactive approach and willingness to learn I feel that the current structure of my training program isn't adequately supporting my development. I want to stress that I genuinely enjoy working for Civmec a company specialising in the field I'm passionate about. I appreciate all the opportunities I've had and can see endless possibilities for growth and advancement within the organisation. However I believe that with additional support and guidance I could contribute even more effectively to the company's success. Therefore I would appreciate the opportunity to discuss these issues further and explore potential solutions that will enable me to fulfil my training requirements effectively. I'm open to any adjustments or alternative approaches that may better align with the objectives of my apprenticeship and facilitate my professional growth. Thank you for your attention to this matter. I look forward to your prompt response and to the opportunity to collaborate on resolving these challenges. Sincerely Derek Guthrie PDF Loaded to docs

EMP_REVIEWNOTES: 29/02/2024 - Site Visit - First and Final Written Warning issued by Natasha Nardone: Reason for Warning: 	Brendan's attitude towards colleagues Supervision and allocated work continues to be poor and a challenge to manage on site. 	This impact on others has resulted in Brendan being removed from 4 of the 7 sites across the Project (Attached emails of a few - see Documents and Contact History Tabs) 	One site is currently the key Apprenticeship site with the training ground and Trainer is Section 11 (Andrew Crew) and after repeated incidents of attitude and poor safety/listening to instruction the Trainer had to remove Brendan from Machine Operating training forcing Brendan to the S11 labouring crew for the foreseeable future which was also the last work option available. 	As per the Attached email and below snippet Brendan continue to not meet the required standards on site while in the labouring crew which escalated to the misconduct of property damage to a Project vehicle which led to Brendan's stand down on 21 February 2024 while his future with SWGA can be considered. PIP Details: 1.	No unauthorised absences from work. Communication around attendance to be clear positive and well planned. 	Intention to take leave needs to be well communicated and made in advance to Skill Hire (as his employer) and to the immediate Supervisor (and other person as appropriate  for example Trainer). 	Communication to be made verbally and in writing to the relevant person(s) including immediate supervisor and Skill Hire representative. This includes unplanned or unexpected leave. A text message to be used as a last resort where verbal communication is not a viable option. 	Leave to be planned well in advance where appropriate adhering to the process for leave request. o	In the event it is unplanned leave communication should occur to immediate supervisor skill hire and relevant person BEFORE prestart. 2.	Bring a can-do attitude to ALL work instructions particularly instructions form those he may not agree with but are safe to undertake and are considered to be lawful instruction. 3.	Show respect to others  particularly supervision specifically Andrew Crew. His relationship with Andrew will need to be established from the outset. 4.	Must show a willingness to accept instruction and work with enthusiasm. 5.	Attend each day fit for work prior to pre-start commencing. 	Communicating any barriers to attending work immediately and in a timely fashion. 	Repeated non-attendance or problematic lateness to work will not be tolerated.
